OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G1/13
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCThe BBC: a universal service
OL,4,Cthat's no longer universally paid for
OL,5,
OL,6,FThere is one thing that is profoundly
OL,7,Fdepressing about the BBC cuts.
OL,9,FThey are not happening under the watch
OL,10,Fof an upstart government which is
OL,11,Fideologically hostile to the supposedly
OL,12,Fwoke BBC, public service broadcasting
OL,13,For public funding.
OL,15,FNor are they happening under a
OL,16,Fmainstream centre right government
OL,17,Fwhich may question the scope of BBC
OL,18,Fservices or promote tight budget
OL,19,Fsettlements to drive efficiency.
OL,21,FThey reflect a fundamental funding
OL,22,Fchallenge.
OL,23,EPub: 20-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,152,140,200,120,0,100
PN,15102
SC,0002
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F151A1784144490
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G2/13
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCThe BBC: a universal service
OL,4,Cthat's no longer universally paid for
OL,5,
OL,6,FIt is not about the level of the TV
OL,7,FLicence. It is about the fact a growing
OL,8,Fnumber of households do not have a
OL,9,Flicence.
OL,11,FDo not mistake this with simple
OL,12,Fhostility to the corporation.
OL,14,FDo you honestly believe that everyone
OL,15,Fwho accesses the iPlayer has a TV
OL,16,FLicence?
OL,18,FI have often wondered if there is a way
OL,19,Fof tightening up access? Perhaps a full
OL,20,Fregistration scheme to make it
OL,21,Fimpossible to access the iPlayer
OL,22,Fwithout a licence.
OL,23,EPub: 20-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,152,140,200,120,0,100
PN,15103
SC,0003
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F151A1784144490
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G3/13
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCThe BBC: a universal service
OL,4,Cthat's no longer universally paid for
OL,5,
OL,6,FYou do not need to be a genius in
OL,7,Fcybercrime to work out how to use the
OL,8,FiPlayer dishonestly. This needs sorted.
OL,10,FFundamentally the BBC is a universal
OL,11,Fservice but it is no longer universally
OL,12,Fpaid for.
OL,14,FA portion of people who are simply
OL,15,Fdodgers are being subsidised by the
OL,16,Frest of us.
OL,23,EPub: 20-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,152,140,200,120,0,100
PN,15104
SC,0004
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F151A1784144490
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G4/13
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCThe BBC: a universal service
OL,4,Cthat's no longer universally paid for
OL,5,
OL,6,FDo not confuse them with libertarians
OL,7,Ftaking some principled stand against an
OL,8,Forganisation they dislike. Nor should
OL,9,Fthey be confused with those on a low
OL,10,Fincome for whom the licence fee may
OL,11,Fgenuinely be a big ask.
OL,13,FThe government needs to urgently decide
OL,14,Fon the best way to secure the BBC's
OL,15,Ffuture.
OL,17,FA household charge for public service
OL,18,Fmedia seems the most sensible option.
OL,20,FIt can be levied with the council tax
OL,21,Fin England, Wales and Scotland. This
OL,22,Fwould make non payment much harder.
OL,23,EPub: 20-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,152,140,200,120,0,100
PN,15105
SC,0005
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F151A1784144490
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G5/13
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCThe BBC: a universal service
OL,4,Cthat's no longer universally paid for
OL,5,
OL,6,FThis also means the level of the charge
OL,7,Fcould be varied ` the higher your
OL,8,Fcouncil tax, the more you pay.
OL,10,FThe practical details ` such as how it
OL,11,Fmight work in Northern Ireland without
OL,12,Fthe council tax ` can be discussed.
OL,14,FAs for the cuts themselves, they can be
OL,15,Fthe subject of a more nuanced
OL,16,Fconversation.
OL,18,FAny organisation can become more
OL,19,Fefficient. I'm sure that even the BBC's
OL,20,Fbiggest supporters would not claim it
OL,21,Fis always as efficient as it could be.
OL,23,EPub: 20-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,152,140,200,120,0,100
PN,15106
SC,0006
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F151A1784144490
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G6/13
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCThe BBC: a universal service
OL,4,Cthat's no longer universally paid for
OL,5,
OL,6,FToo many bureaucrats? Too many people
OL,7,Fon particular teams while others have
OL,8,Ftoo few? Specific working practices?
OL,10,FThat isn't the same as saying the BBC
OL,11,Fis inefficient or wastes money.
OL,12,FFundamentally it is not and does not.
OL,14,FAsk anyone who works for the BBC what
OL,15,Fsort of hotels they can stay in when
OL,16,Fthey're away overnight filming or how
OL,17,Fmuch they can claim for their lunch.
OL,19,FIf any compulsory redundancies are
OL,20,Fcontemplated amongst the rank and file,
OL,21,Fexpect strikes. Jobs must be protected.
OL,23,EPub: 20-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,152,140,200,120,0,100
